kubectl get pod -o yaml 
kubectl get pods -o wide
-o â†’ --output, --output wide
-------------------------------------
Q. argo cd requires only manifest files not a application files at the end argo cd want only docker images ?
--> Argo CD does NOT need your application source code (like HTML, Python, Java code, etc.). 
It needs only Kubernetes manifests OR Helm charts from a Git repository.
-------------------------------------------------------
You need CI/CD pipeline Jenkins to build & push Docker images to docker hub registry.
--------------------------
Argo CD requires only manifest files from Git --> Yes
---------------
via port forward cmd in k8s I can access that output via local host ?
--> Yes! When you use port forwarding in Kubernetes, you can access the application via localhost on your machine.
kubectl port-forward pod/my-pod 8080:80
http://localhost:8080
Port forward works only while the terminal command is running. If you close the terminal, access will stop.
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Q. ingress vs ingress controller ? we need to write only ingress.yaml file not a ingress controller yaml ?
--> ðŸ‘‰ Ingress is only a configuration (rules)
ðŸ‘‰ Ingress Controller is the tool that applies those rules

Without an ingress controller, your ingress file will not work âŒ
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Self-managed K8s cluster --> You install NGINX Ingress Controller via helm 
helm install ingress-nginx ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx --namespace ingress-nginx --create-namespace
kind: Ingress ( networking ) routing rules
--------------------------------
Q. if I m using application load balancer with ingress controller so how to install ingress contoller
--> install AWS ALB Ingress Controller 
ALB Ingress Controller (AWS Load Balancer Controller) Installation on EKS :
Step 1: Install IAM Policy Create IAM policy
Step 2: Create IAM Role for EKS Service Account
Step 3: Install CRDs for the ALB Ingress Controller --> Custom Resource Definition (CRD)
Install via Helm --> helm install aws-load-balancer-controller eks/aws-load-balancer-controller
Annotation: kubernetes.io/ingress.class: alb
--------------------------------------------------
ðŸŽ¯ Final Summary
âœ” If using Application Load Balancer + Ingress, you MUST install AWS Load Balancer Controller
âœ” It creates ALB automatically using ingress rules
âœ” You only write ingress.yaml, NOT controller YAML
-----------------------------------------------------------------
Q. in argocd kind : application there is source and destination what is that ?
ðŸ”¹ source â†’ Where your Kubernetes manifests/Helm charts are stored --> git repo 
Git repository with Kubernetes files (deployment, service, ingress etc.)
ArgoCD reads this and deploys it.
ðŸ”¹ destination â†’ Where your application will be deployed (which cluster + namespace) --> eks cluster
--------------------------------------------------
apiVersion: argoproj.io/v1alpha1
kind: Application
metadata:
  name: myapp
  namespace: argocd
spec:
  source:
    repoURL: https://github.com/ramesh/myapp-manifests.git
    targetRevision: main     # branch name
    path: k8s/               # folder where YAML files are stored

  destination:
    server: https://kubernetes.default.svc   # EKS / Local cluster
    namespace: myapp-namespace

  project: default
  syncPolicy:
    automated:
      prune: true
      selfHeal: true
